You are given a function:
int CheckPassword(char str[], int n, int min);

The function will accept a string (str[]), its length (n), and another argument min, which denotes the minimum length of the password. You are supposed to print "valid" if the password meets the criteria given below, or "invalid" if the password does not meet the criteria.

Password criteria:
At least min characters long
At least one numeric digit
At least one capital letter
At least one special character
Must not contain a space or the + character
The starting character must not be a number

Write code to check if the password meets these requirements.

Assumption:
Input string will not be empty.

Example:

Input1:
aB1_72&
5
Output1:
Valid

Input1:
c281 pbY012!
2
Output1:
Invalid